                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14411563" author="brettporter" created="Thu, 7 Jun 2007 04:01:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;will review patch for 2.0.7 since it has a test and all&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14411787" author="brettporter" created="Thu, 7 Jun 2007 04:05:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;my bad, it&apos;s just the test - no fix yet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14411800" author="brettporter" created="Thu, 7 Jun 2007 04:32:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch applied for test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14420774" author="sleberrigaud" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2007 18:50:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sounds like a critical issue to me. It is &lt;em&gt;impossible&lt;/em&gt; to work with multi-module projects if dependencies resolution goes to the repositories instead of the reactor. An good example of this is working with the release plugin (version 2.0-beta-7 IIRC):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. I do a clean checkout on a build server,&lt;br/&gt;
2. I run mvn release:prepare&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And as release:prepare relies on the @requiresDependencyResolution, it fails because the SNAPSHOT is not installed locally.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14414093" author="brettporter" created="Thu, 18 Dec 2008 05:19:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this constantly proves a nuisance - worth reviewing&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14414362" author="jdcasey" created="Mon, 9 Feb 2009 09:35:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Consolidating to 2.1.0-M1 so we can then rename to 2.1.0. We can weed out any issues we want to push to a later release from this set once we&apos;ve done the consolidation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14414892" author="zac" created="Tue, 16 Jun 2009 12:40:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I still see this behaviour in 2.1.0. (Samuel&apos;s example above)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;... update: actually, I think this is because of a test dependency, which is posted as a different issue.  My apologies!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17998137" author="JIRAUSER302100" created="Sat, 5 Jul 2025 13:03:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven/issues/4862&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven#4862&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
